Things I do in my 30s and wish I should have started in my 20s. 

Things I do in my 30s that I wish I started earlier👇
— Early dinners (6:30-7PM) = better sleep & digestion
— Double cleansing > over-cleansing
— 5 go-to makeup staples. No hoarding.
— Amla + curry leaves + ginger water = gut & immunity boost
— Pilates + weights + cardio = balance, strength & energy

I felt my absolute low and a body that was mostly lethargic. And what a glow up 30s got me! The mental shift, the physical shift, all on point. And moreover, a take on decluttering and minimize things wherever possible. From a makeup hoarder, a no gym BS to making it a part of life, all so nicely.

Try it! for more self growth and minimalist style content follow @thepslife_

“You’ve changed.” Yes — and thank god I did.
But some things? I held on to them — even when the world told me to let them go. My voice. My sensitivity. My dreams. My way of loving. My pace. My style.
If you’ve ever been told to change just to fit in — I hope you didn’t. Because life in your 30s hits different when you finally own every part of who you are.
✨ Save this if you’re growing, healing, and still holding on to what matters. ✨ Tag the women who made you feel seen — even in the mess.

This book has been so interesting and eye-opening. I used to think I wanted that designer bag, that body, that life. 

📖 this highly recommended book Wanting by Luke Burgis cracked something open: We don’t chase dreams—we chase validation. We want what others want, and then call it ambition.
If you’ve ever felt weirdly restless after scrolling, or suddenly wanted to switch careers because your peer just got a raise—
 this reel is your wake-up call.

It’s not your fault. But it is your responsibility to unlearn. 
Start by asking: Do I really want this… or do I want to be wanted?

What if I tell you, you don’t need 100 outfits to look stylish? These 5 wardrobe basics are the real heroes I wear on repeat — no trends, no fluff, just timeless pieces that work every time.

✨ Breezy everyday denim ✨ White non-see-through T-shirt ✨ Pure cotton button-down ✨ Oversized tee for effortless layers ✨ My go-to sneakers: Adidas Sambas

Basics were and are worn by icons like Steve Jobs, Jennifer Aniston, Meghan Markle, and Matilda Djerf—a simplified wardrobe isn’t just chic; it’s smart.
Tell me your most worn item right now — I bet it’s not a trendy piece either.

Friendships hit different in your 30s.
You’re juggling careers, raising kids, managing homes, showing up for parents—and sometimes, just trying to stay afloat.❤️💫

So yes, plans get cancelled. Texts go unanswered. You disappear into your own life.
But the friendships that last? They don’t need explanations. They feel easy, grounding, and real.

No pressure to perform. No guilt-trips. Just soft, quiet understanding.
Here’s to the ones who still check in. Still show up. Still feel like home—even after weeks of silence.
